-- Hugo Boss to Open as Many as 60 New Stores This Year, Handelsblatt Reports
-- Andreas Cremer
-- 2010-06-22T06:10:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/hugo-boss-to-open-as-many-as-60-new-stores-this-year-handelsblatt-says.html

          
          
             Hugo Boss AG  aims to open as many as
60 new shops per year, a third of which will be in China, to
help raise sales,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing Chief Executive
Officer Claus-Dietrich Lahrs.  
 Hugo Boss wants to increase the share of sales stemming
from shops and Web-based retail to about 50 percent by 2015 from
33 percent last year, the newspaper said.  
